Uses of Package
be.signalsync.slicer

  • Packages that use be.signalsync.slicer 
    Package Description
    be.signalsync.slicer
    This package contains all the classes used for slicing Streams and StreamSets.
    be.signalsync.stream
    This package contains classes used for representing, converting, creating and processing streams.
    be.signalsync.sync
    This package contains the classes used to invoke and process the synchronization.
  • Classes in be.signalsync.slicer used by be.signalsync.slicer 
    Class and Description
    SliceEvent
    This class contains a slice and metadata about a slice.
    SliceListener
    This interface has to be implemented when an instance is interested in slice data of a Stream or StreamSet.
    Slicer
    The supertype of the different types of Slicers.
  • Classes in be.signalsync.slicer used by be.signalsync.stream 
    Class and Description
    Sliceable
    Any implementing class has to be able to create a Slicer.
    StreamSetSlicer
    This class is a Slicer used to take slices of different streams wrapped in a StreamSet.
    StreamSlicer
    This class is a concrete Slicer which can create float[] slices of a Stream.
  • Classes in be.signalsync.slicer used by be.signalsync.sync 
    Class and Description
    SliceEvent
    This class contains a slice and metadata about a slice.
    SliceListener
    This interface has to be implemented when an instance is interested in slice data of a Stream or StreamSet.
    Slicer
    The supertype of the different types of Slicers.
